definition:
A man of the tribe of Issachar living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.7.3; 
 son of: Uzzi (H5813H); 
 father of: Michael (H4317K), Obadiah (H5662I), Joel (H3100L) and Isshiah (H3449)
 § Izrahiah or Jezrahiah = "Jehovah will shine"
1) a chieftain of Issachar
2) a Levite and leader of the chorus at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem under Nehemiah
